00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:52,040
Yeah, last year.
是的，最后一年。

170
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:53,560
My last year of college.
我大学的最后一年。

171
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:54,560
Exactly.
没错。

172
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:55,560
Very good.
非常好。

173
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:59,720
So, now you know how you can explain to someone what year of college or university you're
所以，现在你知道如何向别人解释你上大学的第几年了，

174
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,720
in.
对吧。

175
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:01,720
Yes, that's right.
是的，没错。

176
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:02,720
Very good.
非常好。

177
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:03,880
And we have one more phrase to you.
我们还有一个短语要告诉你。

178
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:07,000
And it was when she was getting her class schedule.
就是当她拿到课程表的时候。

179
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,960
So, class schedule.
所以，课程表。

180
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:10,960
Class schedule.
课程表。

181
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:16,040
Now, a schedule is the list of things you do at what time.
现在，课程表就是你什么时间做什么事情的一个列表。

182
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:20,560
Right, so it's the timetable of your day or your week.
对，所以它就是你一天或一周的时间表。

183
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:21,560
Yep.
嗯。

184
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:22,560
All right.
好的。

185
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:26,560
So, your class schedule will say all the classes that you have and what time they're at.
所以，你的课程表会列出你所有的课程以及它们的时间。

186
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:30,400
So, what other types of schedules can we have?
那么，我们还能有其他什么类型的日程表呢？

187
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,640
You also have maybe a gym schedule.
你可能还有健身计划。

188
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:33,640
That's right.
没错。

189
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:35,160
Or even a work schedule.
或者甚至工作安排。

190
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:36,160
Right.
对。

191
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:40,680
So, we have different types of schedules and you can use it depending on what you are doing.
所以，我们有不同类型的日程表，你可以根据你正在做的事情来使用它们。

192
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:44,000
Those are all the phrases we have for putting it together today.
这些就是我们今天要整合的所有短语。

193
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:57,840
And now, let's listen to the dialogue for the last time and then we'll come back.
现在，让我们最后一次听对话，然后我们再回来。

194
00:09:57,840 --> 00:09:58,840
Excuse me.
打扰一下。

195
00:09:58,840 --> 00:09:59,840
Is this where I register?
这是注册的地方吗？

196
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:02,280
I'd like to sign up for my courses for next semester.
我想报名下学期的课程。

197
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:03,760
Yes, of course.
是的，当然。

198
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:06,440
I need your student ID, please.
我需要你的学生证。

199
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,880
Here you are.
给你。

200
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:10,320
Okay, Susan.
好的，苏珊。

201
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:13,800
It says here that you are a business major and that you're in your second year.
这里写着你的专业是商科，而且你正在读大二。

202
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:15,400
Is this information correct?
这个信息正确吗？

203
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,400
Yes.
是的。

204
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:20,200
I do want to take some additional credits this year to get a minor in psychology.
我今年确实想多修一些学分，辅修心理学。

205
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,200
Sure.
当然可以。

206
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:22,200
That's not a problem.
这没问题。

207
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:24,720
Do you have a list of courses that you want to take this semester?
你这学期想选的课程清单有吗？

208
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:25,720
Yeah.
有。

209
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:27,280
Here's my list.
这是我的清单。

210
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:30,760
I'm not sure if the class schedule will allow me to take all of them, though.
不过我不确定课程表能不能让我全部选上。

211
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:32,040
Yeah, that's perfect.
嗯，那很好。

212
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:33,640
What about the subjects for your minor?
那你辅修的科目呢？

213
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:34,640
Oh, yeah.
哦，对了。

214
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:36,160
I almost forgot.
我差点忘了。

215
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:40,800
I need to take fundamental linguistics, consumer psychology, and neuroanatomy.
我需要修基础语言学、消费者心理学和神经解剖学。

216
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:41,800
Wow.
哇。

217
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:44,200
You're going to be busy this semester.
你这学期要忙起来了。

218
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:48,800
Okay, here you go.
好了，给你。

219
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:49,800
You're registered now.
你现在已经注册好了。

220
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:53,960
You have to make your first tuition payment before classes start.
你必须在开课前支付第一笔学费。

221
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:59,360
All right.
好的。

222
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:03,080
So we were talking about second year, first year, third year, etc.
所以我们刚才在聊大二、大一、大三等等。

223
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,080
Yeah.
嗯。

224
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:09,960
Now, there are also other names that we give to each year, both for high school and university.
现在，对于每个年级，无论是高中还是大学，我们还有其他的叫法。

225
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:13,880
And I think this is only for America.
而且我觉得这只有美国才用。

226
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:18,440
Like in the United States, we don't do this in Canada, and I always get so confused.
比如在美国是这样，但在加拿大我们不这么叫，我总是搞混。

227
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:22,760
So Marco, what is the name you give to first year students?
那么，Marco，大一学生叫什么？

228
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:25,800
Okay, so first year students are called freshmen.
好的，大一学生叫freshmen。

229
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:27,200
Okay, because they're fresh.
嗯，因为他们很新鲜（fresh）。

230
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,200
Because they're fresh.
因为他们很新鲜。

231
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,440
Yeah, they just came from middle school, they just came from high school.
是啊，他们刚从初中或高中毕业过来。

232
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:31,440
All right.
好的。

233
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,440
And what about the second year students?
那大二学生呢？

234
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,440
They're called sophomores.
他们叫sophomores。

235
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:34,440
Okay, because they're soft.
嗯，因为他们很软（soft）。

236
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,440
Well, it's not soft.
呃，不是软。

237
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,440
It's a sophomore.
是sophomore。

238
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:42,440
Like S-O-P-H.
拼写是S-O-P-H。

239
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,440
Sophomore.
Sophomore。

240
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:44,440
Sophomore.
Sophomore。

241
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:45,920
And then third year students are called juniors.
然后大三学生叫juniors。

242
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:49,960
Okay, because they're almost the, like junior manager.
嗯，因为他们差不多是，比如初级经理。

243
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:50,960
Exactly.
没错。

244
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:54,040
Because then last year students are called seniors.
因为最后一年学生叫seniors。

245
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:56,640
So the oldest guys in the school.
所以是学校里最年长的家伙。

246
00:11:56,640 --> 00:11:57,640
Exactly.
没错。

247
00:11:57,640 --> 00:12:01,520
So you can say, yeah, I'm a sophomore at Arizona State University.
所以你可以说，是啊，我是亚利桑那州立大学的大二学生。

248
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:04,200
Okay, so we only use this in America though, right?
好的，但这只有美国用，对吧？

249
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,200
Yes, yes.
是的，是的。

250
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:09,600
And not only for university, but also for high school.
而且不仅大学，高中也用。

251
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:10,600
Okay.
好的。

252
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:13,000
All right, guys, that's all the time we have for today.
好了，各位，我们今天的节目时间就到这里。

253
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,840
I hope you enjoyed this lesson.
希望你们喜欢这节课。

254
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:19,600
And if you have any questions or comments or you want to share with us your experiences
如果你们有任何问题、评论，或者想和我们分享你们在高中或大学的经历，

255
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:25,000
in high school or university, please come to the website at EnglishPod.com.
请访问我们的网站EnglishPod.com。

256
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,000
That's right.
没错。

257
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,000
So Marco and I are there to answer your questions.
我和Marco会在那里回答你们的问题。

258
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,000
